As a clinical decision support system, generate a systemic/infectious workup:
1. Top differentials for constitutional symptoms (infection, malignancy, autoimmune, endocrine, hematologic)
2. Fever workup (blood cultures x2, UA/UCx, CXR, CBC with differential, CRP/ESR/procalcitonin)
3. Fatigue workup (TSH, CBC, CMP, iron studies, B12/folate, cortisol, HIV, mono spot)
4. Weight loss workup (CT chest/abdomen/pelvis, age-appropriate cancer screening, A1c, TSH)
5. SIRS/sepsis criteria evaluation (temp >38.3°C or <36°C, HR >90, RR >20, WBC >12k or <4k)
6. Infection control and isolation considerations
7. Empiric therapy if sepsis suspected (blood cultures → broad spectrum antibiotics within 1 hour)

